     (a) (a) absol.; Mk 1:4, Jo 1:25,  26 28 3:22, 23, 26 4:2 10:40, I Co 1:17; ὁ βαπτίζων (= ὁ βαπτιστής, M, Pr., 127), Mk 6:14, 24; c. acc., Jo 4:1, Ac 8:38, I Co 
1:14, 16; c. cogn. acc., τὸ βάπτισμα, Ac 19:4 (cf. Mk 10:38, supr.); pass., to be baptized, receive baptism: Mt 3:13, 14, 16, Mk 16:16, Lk 3:7,  12 21 7:29 (τ. βάπτισμα) ib. 30, Ac 2:41  8:12,  13 36 9:18 10:47 16:15, 33 18:8; mid., 22:16 (M, Pr., 163); 
