 [NT: 9018x] 
καί, 
conj.,  
 and 
  I. Copulative.  
    1. Connecting single words; 
      (a) in general: Mt 2:18, 16:1, Mk 2:15, Lk 8:15, He 1:1, al. mult.; repeated before each of the terms in a series, Mt 23:23, Lk 14:21, Ro 7:12, 9:4, al. 
