     (b) in ethical sense, esp. in Pauline Epp., of the flesh as the seat and vehicle of sinful desires: opp. to νοῦς, Ro 7:25; to πνεῦμα, Ro 8:4-9, 12, 13, Ga 5:16,  17 19 6:8 (cf. DB, ii, 14f.; iv, 165f.; Cremer, 844ff.).

